      "author": "sharkello",
      "description": "## What's new in 1.2.0\n\n**Pull new pages from Notion**\nPages created directly in Notion now appear in Obsidian. Use the folder-down button in the sync panel or the command Pull new pages from Notion.\n\n**Status bar**\nLive indicator at the bottom of Obsidian: Ready / Syncing... / Synced 3m ago / Sync error.\n\n**File Explorer indicators**\nSynced files show a green checkmark. Locally modified files show an orange M — just like git status in VS Code.\n\n**Download images on Pull**\nNotion images are downloaded to a local _attachments folder and replaced with Obsidian embeds. Toggle in Settings → Download Images on Pull.\n\n**Progress bar**\nVisual progress bar in the sync panel during full vault sync and pull operations.\n\n**Sync History + Rollback**\nThe history button in the sync panel shows the last 100 push/pull operations. Pull operations include a Rollback button to instantly restore the file to its previous state.",
