      "author": "sharkello",
      "description": "## What's new in 1.1.0\n\n### Sync Panel (left ribbon icon)\n- Click the **upload-cloud** icon in the left ribbon to open the Notion Sync side panel\n- Toolbar buttons mirroring VS Code's Source Control panel:\n  - **Push** group: Sync Entire Vault, Sync Changed Files, Sync Current Note\n  - **Pull** group: Pull All Notes ← Notion, Pull Current Note ← Notion\n  - Log button: Open Sync Log\n\n### Bidirectional sync (Pull from Notion)\n- Pull individual note or all mapped notes back from Notion to Obsidian\n- Smart conflict detection: if both local file and Notion page changed since last sync, the file is **not** overwritten — you get a warning to resolve manually\n- New commands: `Pull current note from Notion`, `Pull all notes from Notion`\n\n### Bug fix\n- **Fixed**: switching sync mode to Manual no longer leaves the OnSave file watcher active (files were syncing automatically even in Manual mode)",
